General.Name: Grong Sparebank
General.Description: Grong Sparebank, an independent savings bank, provides a range of banking products and services in Norway. It offers bank savings accounts; fund savings; retirement savings; and car loans, mortgage loans, loans to other vehicles, and other loans and refinancing services. The company also provides various type of insurance, such as home and leisure, car and other vehicle, animal, building, mortgage, employee, and business insurance; bank guarantees, construction loans, overdrafts, leasing facilities, and corporate loans; credit facilities; payment and bank cards, and Internet and mobile banking services; and real estate agency services. It has branches in Snåsa, Lierne, Mosjøen, Namsos, Steinkjer, and Rørvik. Grong Sparebank was founded in 1862 and is based in Grong, Norway.
